.\" termin.al-name: projects
.\" termin.al-usage: projects
.\" termin.al-summary: Open projects content.
.TH PROJECTS 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
projects \- Open projects content.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
projects
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens the validated project README collection associated with the virtual
.B ~/projects
target. Rows are grouped by project collection path and show project name, repository metadata and tags; Enter opens the supplied rendered README.
.SH VIEWER
Use j/k or arrows to move, h/l or left/right to collapse and expand, g/G or Home/End to jump, Enter to toggle/open, and / to filter. An external repository link opens separately when activated. q, Escape or Ctrl+C returns from the collection; returning from a README restores the selector. Mobile controls expose movement, filtering, opening and Shell return.
.SH FAILURES
Extra arguments are rejected. If the virtual projects directory is missing, path resolution fails. Cancellation opens nothing.
.SH NOTES
Project rows come from validated project metadata rather than by reading arbitrary files from the projects directory. The viewer is read-only and transient; returning preserves the owning shell state.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ projects
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
open(1), blog(1), notes(1)
